## Structured Logging

Structured logs (JSON) are machine-parseable and far easier to query than free-text logs:

```java
// Bad — free text, hard to query
log.info("Order 123 processed in 45ms for user alice");

// Good — structured JSON
log.info("Order processed",
    "orderId", orderId,
    "durationMs", elapsed,
    "userId", userId,
    "status", "SUCCESS");
// Output: {"msg":"Order processed","orderId":"123","durationMs":45,"userId":"alice",...}
```

### MDC (Mapped Diagnostic Context)
```java
// Add trace context to all log lines in this request
MDC.put("traceId", traceId);
MDC.put("userId", userId);
MDC.put("requestId", requestId);
// All subsequent log statements in this thread include these fields
```

## Distributed Tracing

A trace tracks a single request as it flows through multiple services. It's composed of **spans** — one per service or operation.

```
Trace: checkout-flow [total: 450ms]
├─ span: api-gateway [20ms]
├─ span: order-service [180ms]
│   ├─ span: validate-cart [30ms]
│   └─ span: db-write [150ms]
├─ span: payment-service [200ms]
│   ├─ span: fraud-check [80ms]
│   └─ span: stripe-api [120ms]
└─ span: notification-service [50ms]
```

### OpenTelemetry (OTel)
The vendor-neutral standard for instrumentation:

```java
// Auto-instrumentation (no code changes)
// Add -javaagent:opentelemetry-javaagent.jar
// OTel instruments Spring, JDBC, HTTP clients automatically

// Manual span creation
Span span = tracer.spanBuilder("processOrder").startSpan();
try (Scope scope = span.makeCurrent()) {
    span.setAttribute("order.id", orderId);
    processOrder(orderId);
} catch (Exception e) {
    span.recordException(e);
    span.setStatus(StatusCode.ERROR);
} finally {
    span.end();
}
```
